claim.claim-text:
3. A method of using a sonography machine to aid in embryo transfer during in vitro fertilization, comprising:
obtaining a 4D image of a uterine cavity on the sonography machine;
determining a maximal implantation potential point from the image of the uterine cavity as a target for embryo placement within the uterine cavity by determining the intersection point of lines representing the angles at which the fallopian tubes enter the uterine cavity;
obtaining a 4D image of a catheter in the uterine cavity: and
using the image of the catheter to determine when a tip of the catheter is over the maximal implantation potential point for releasing the embryo.
